    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_cæstysyg" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>cæstysyg</orth><form type="variant"
                            ><orth>cæssyg</orth></form></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>cæstisug</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>слеза</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>tear</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>cæstysyg yzǧæly agmæ sūsægæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>слезы тайком падают в котел</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>tears secretly fall into the kettle</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>44</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>stavd cæssygæj kæwy ḱyzg</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>девушка плачет крупными слезами</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a girl is crying big tears</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ЮОПам."/><biblScope>III
                            16</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example xml:lang="os-x-digor">
                        <usg><lang/></usg>
                        <quote>neke ǧæwuncæ mæ cæstisugtæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>никому не нужны мои слезы</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>nobody needs my tears</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Iræf"/><biblScope>12</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>(meǧtæ) sæ ǧar cæstisug wæd ærkaluncæ</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>(тучи) проливают тогда свою теплую слезу</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>(the clouds) then shed their warm tear</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."
                            /><biblScope>56%l98%l</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Буквально „струя (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_syg"/>) глаза
                    (%icæsty%i)“; ср. по образованию <mentioned xml:lang="tg"><lang/>
                        <w n="0">оби-чашм</w>
                        <gloss><q>слеза</q></gloss></mentioned> („вода-глаза“), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kv"><lang/>
                        <w>cin-ba</w>
                        <gloss><q>слеза</q></gloss></mentioned> („глаза- вода“); <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>kʼur-cxali</w>
                        <gloss><q>слеза</q></gloss></mentioned> представляет, по <bibl><author>Н. Я.
                            Марру</author></bibl>, такое же сложение (<mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>*kur</w>
                        <gloss><q>глаз</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"
                            ><w>*cхal</w>
                        <gloss><q>вода</q></gloss></mentioned>). Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>čšwq</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>čškw</w>
                        <gloss><q>слеза</q></gloss></mentioned>. См. <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_cæst"/> и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syg"/>.%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>31,
                        37</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It is literally “jet (<ref type="xr" target="#entry_syg"/>) of
                    the eye (%icæsty%i)”; cf. by the derivation <mentioned xml:lang="tg"><lang/>
                        <w>obi-čašm</w>
                        <gloss><q>tear</q></gloss></mentioned> (“water-eye”), <mentioned
                        xml:lang="kv"><lang/>
                        <w>cin-ba</w>
                        <gloss><q>tear</q></gloss></mentioned> (“eye-water”); <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>kʼur-cxali</w>
                        <gloss><q>tear</q></gloss></mentioned> represents, as <bibl><author>N. Ya.
                            Marr</author></bibl>assumes, the same compound (<mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>*kur</w>
                        <gloss><q>eye</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w>*cхal</w>
                        <gloss><q>water</q></gloss></mentioned>). Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/>
                        <w>čšwq</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>čškw</w>
                        <gloss><q>tear</q></gloss></mentioned>. See <ref type="xr"
                        target="#entry_cæst"/> and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syg"/>.%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>31,
                        37</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
